#Text=Sulphur ( Oklahoma )
#Text=Sulphur is in the Chickasaw Country Region of Oklahoma .
#Text=Understand
#Text=Sulphur , OK has a history dating back before Oklahoma 's statehood in 1907 .
#Text=The town was formed largely due to the popularity of the healing Sulphur Springs in the Chickasaw National Recreation Area , formerly Platt National Park .
#Text=Get in
#Text=Sulphur is easily accessible from I-35 .
#Text=From I-35 , take Exit 55 east toward Davis and continue through Davis on Highway 7 until you reach Sulphur .
#Text=Get around
#Text=Sulphur is mostly a car town , but you can grab a bike at the bike share at the Chickasaw Visitor Center at Hwy 177 and Hwy 7 .
#Text=See
#Text=Lake of the Arbuckles ( Located in the Chickasaw National Recreation Area ) .
#Text=This lake also serves as a reservoir for Murray County .
#Text=Fishing is available for varieties of catfish , perch , bass and crappie .
#Text=Located within the Chickasaw National Recreation Area , there are several camping grounds and RV camps available to rent .
#Text=Facilities include campgrounds , trailer spaces , picnic areas , shelters , tables , public restrooms , drinking water , boat docks and boat ramps .
#Text=Vendome Well ( Located just off Highway 7 near downtown Sulphur in the Chickasaw National Recreation Area ) .
#Text=A symbol of the namesake of Sulphur , Oklahoma , the Vendome Well is a mineral spring that always runs .
#Text=Visitors once came from everywhere to drink the mineral waters from the well .
#Text=There is a spigot where you can still drink the water ( if you can get over the egg smell ) .
#Text=Chickasaw Cultural Center , 867 Cooper Memorial Dr. , ☏ +1580 622-7130 .
#Text=Do
#Text=Chickasaw National Recreation Area .
#Text=Mineral springs , streams , lakes and waterfalls attract visitors from all over the world .
#Text=Chickasaw Visitor Center , 901 W 1st Street , ☏ +1 580-622-8050 . 9:00 a.m. - 6:00 p. m. .
#Text=The Chickasaw Visitor Center stands at the entrance to the Chickasaw National Recreation Area and houses the National Park Service .
#Text=The center offers public restrooms , free refreshments , a bike share program and plenty of travel information and maps for the area if you need ideas on where to go and what to do .
#Text=The small gift shop has a nice selection of souvenirs , including Chickasaw Country products , Native American jewelry and gifts .
#Text=The Chickasaw Visitor Center hosts regular cultural demonstrations as well as a rotating featured artist with art on display and available for purchase .
#Text=Artesian Arts Festival , downtown Sulphur , ☏ +1 580-272-5520 .
#Text=This annual arts festival takes place every Memorial Day weekend in downtown Sulphur .
#Text=Artwork is available from Native and Southwestern artists from across the country .
#Text=Live music from local and traveling artists takes place all day along with a variety of food and retail vendors throughout the festival .
#Text=Art activities and classes are available throughout the day for visitors .
#Text=Free entry .
#Text=Buy
#Text=Third and Broadway ( Downtown ) .
#Text=A small boutique with unique " country " gifts and clothing .
#Text=Spice and Tea Exchange of Sulphur , 8 West Muskogee Ave , ☏ +1 580-622-3770 , ✉ sulphur@spiceandtea.com .
#Text=Sunday 11:00 - 5:00 Monday - Thursday , 11:00 - 6:00 Friday & Saturday , 11:00 - 7:00 .
#Text=A local franchise of a larger chain , Spice and Tea Exchange has a wide variety of unique spices including salts , sugars , peppers , spice blends and teas .
#Text=They also have a small selection of cooking tools available .
#Text=Luxe at the Artesian , 1600 Division ( Located on the east side of the Artesian Hotel ) , ☏ +1 580-622-8908 .
#Text=Sun – Thurs : 9 a.m. – 9 p. m. ; Fri – Sat : 9 a.m. – 11 p. m. .
#Text=This boutique shop carries several high-end designers and has a nice variety of clothing and fashion accessories for men and women .
#Text=The Mix Mercantile , 300 West Muskogee , ☏ +1 580-232-2260 ext 1 .
#Text=Tues - Sat : 10 am - 5:30 pm .
#Text=Family-owned boutique in the downtown district that sells apparel , jewelry , accessories , home décor and gourmet food items .
#Text=Eat
#Text=Flower Bluff Mansion Steakhouse , 329 W Muskogee Ave ( Downtown ) , ☏ +1580 622-4005 .
#Text=Wednesday through Saturday 5-9pm .
#Text=High-end dining .
#Text=The classy atmosphere provides an intimate dining experience .
#Text=Reservations recommended , walk-ins welcome .
#Text=Springs at the Artesian ( Springs ) , 1001 W. 1st Street ( Located inside The Artesian Hotel ) , ☏ +1 580-622-8106 .
#Text=Sun - Thurs : 7 a.m. – 10 p.m. Fri - Sat : 7 a.m. – 11 p. m. .
#Text=This restaurant offers southern comfort food in a fine dining setting .
#Text=Dishes include items like chicken-fried steak , fried green tomatoes , and catfish .
#Text=Reservations are recommended due to high-volume traffic on weekends .
#Text=Bedré Cafe , 14 West Muskogee ( Located on the south side of the Artesian Hotel ) , ☏ +1 580-622-8020 .
#Text=Daily : 6:00 a.m. – 8:00 p. m. .
#Text=This diner-themed café offers deli sandwiches , soups , salads and desserts .
#Text=They also carry the full line of Bedré Fine Chocolate and have a wide range of ice cream products .
#Text=Drink
#Text=The Rusty Nail Winery , 218 W Muskogee Ave , ☏ +1580 622-8466 .
#Text=Tuesday - Saturday : 12 - 8 p. m. , Closed Sunday and Monday .
#Text=The Rusty Nail is a family-owned boutique winery and gift shop .
#Text=The name comes from the former resident at the same location , which was a hardware store .
#Text=They do n't grow their own grapes , but instead ferment their wine from juice blends and offer sweet and dry wines as well as white , blush and red .
#Text=There is a small food menu available .
#Text=The Fountain Club ( Inside The Artesian Hotel ) , ☏ +1 580-622-8107 .
#Text=Sunday through Thursday : 3 p.m. – 12 a.m.
#Text=Friday through Saturday : 12 p.m. – 1:30 a. m. .
#Text=Beer , wine and classic cocktails with live entertainment every Friday night .
#Text=They also have a limited food menu available .
#Text=Sleep
#Text=Artesian Hotel , Casino & Spa ( The Artesian ) , 1001 W. 1st Street , ☏ +1-855-455-5255 .
#Text=Check-in : 4 p. m. , check-out : 12 p. m. .
#Text=This hotel is a revival of an iconic historic hotel destroyed in the 1960s by fire .
#Text=Rebuilt and reopened by the Chickasaw Nation in 2013 , the hotel 's architecture mimics that of the original hotel .
#Text=Amenities include an on-site spa , restaurant , bar , casino , fitness center , two pools , a bath house and a wide variety of boutique shopping options .
#Text=Rooms start at $ 139 .
#Text=Chickasaw Retreat and Conference Center , 4205 Goddard Youth Camp Road , ☏ +1-855-899-8260 .
#Text=Located just outside the Chickasaw National Recreation Area , this hotel offers excellent views of the surrounding Arbuckle Mountains .
#Text=Amenities include fitness center , swimming pool and bar .
#Text=The center provides several offerings for business and family groups .
#Text=Prices start at $ 129 .
#Text=Echo Canyon , 350 Lawton Avenue , ☏ +1 580-421-5076 .
#Text=Locally owned spa resort .
